Following this basic idea, a procedure for computing the SC metric is presented in [7], [8] and it is briefly described here:


1)
Obtain an estimate of the Pareto front \${\cal P}_{y}\$; 2) Normalize all objectives to [0], [1];


3)
3) Define a radius \$\rho\$ in the objective space;


4)
Place a sphere of radius \$\rho\$ centered at any point of the estimate set;


5)
Initialize a sphere count as equal to one;


6)
Exclude all points which are located within this sphere;



7)
Among the remaining points, center the sphere at the point that is the closest one to the previous center and increment the sphere count;


8)
Go to step 5 until there is no more remaining points in the estimate set;
.

